Governor of the province Zhang Zuoji on Thursday warned locals as well as animal husbandry against using water from the polluted Songhua River.
Zhang said the government will step up crackdown on polluting enterprises, noting 2,682 polluting plants have been shut down from May last year to September this year.
Songhua River will carry poisonous substances to Harbin, a major city in northeast China, at round 5:00 a.m. Thursday, an official said at a press conference Wednesday afternoon.